00:13:04.460 --> 00:13:07.950
and move on to where we are now.

00:13:07.950 --> 00:13:13.770
OK, so last time we
talked about scattering

00:13:13.770 --> 00:13:16.950
of a particle, a quantum
particle of mass m

00:13:16.950 --> 00:13:19.322
against a barrier.

00:13:19.322 --> 00:13:20.780
And we made a
classical prediction,

00:13:20.780 --> 00:13:22.180
which I didn't quite
phrase this way.

00:13:22.180 --> 00:13:23.596
But we made a
classical prediction

00:13:23.596 --> 00:13:27.640
that if you took this
particle of mass m

00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:29.880
and threw it against a
barrier of height v0,

00:13:29.880 --> 00:13:32.180
that the probability
that it will transmit

00:13:32.180 --> 00:13:37.135
across this barrier to
infinity is basically 0.

00:13:37.135 --> 00:13:38.635
So this is the
classical prediction.

00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:47.390
It will not transmit to
infinity until the energy goes

00:13:47.390 --> 00:13:48.927
above the potential.

00:13:48.927 --> 00:13:51.510
And when the energy is above the
potential, it will slow down,

00:13:51.510 --> 00:13:53.720
but it will transmit
100% of the time.

00:13:59.871 --> 00:14:01.370
So this is our
classical prediction.

00:14:04.340 --> 00:14:06.840
And so we sought to solve
this problem, we did.

00:14:06.840 --> 00:14:08.260
It was pretty straightforward.

00:14:08.260 --> 00:14:11.555
And the energy eigenstate
took the form-- well,

00:14:11.555 --> 00:14:12.930
we know how to
solve it out here,

00:14:12.930 --> 00:14:13.940
we know how to
solve it out here,

00:14:13.940 --> 00:14:15.900
because these are just
constant potentials

00:14:15.900 --> 00:14:18.420
so it's just plain waves.

00:14:18.420 --> 00:14:20.130
Let's take the
case of the energy

00:14:20.130 --> 00:14:22.920
is less than the potential.

00:14:22.920 --> 00:14:23.760
So this guy.

00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:26.027
Then out here, it's in a
classically disallowed state,

00:14:26.027 --> 00:14:27.360
so it's got to be a exponential.

00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:29.026
If we want it to be
normalized, well, we

00:14:29.026 --> 00:14:30.575
need it to be a
decaying exponential.

00:14:30.575 --> 00:14:32.200
Out here it's
oscillatory, because it's

00:14:32.200 --> 00:14:33.610
a classically allowed region.

00:14:33.610 --> 00:14:36.610
And so the general form of the
wave function of the energy

00:14:36.610 --> 00:14:40.320
eigenstate is a superposition
of a wave moving this way

00:14:40.320 --> 00:14:42.960
with positive momentum, a
wave with negative momentum,

00:14:42.960 --> 00:14:45.700
a contribution with
minus k, and out here it

00:14:45.700 --> 00:14:47.370
had to be the
decaying exponential.

00:14:47.370 --> 00:14:50.210
And then by matching, requiring
that the wave function was

00:14:50.210 --> 00:14:53.480
oscillatory and then
exponentially decaying out

00:14:53.480 --> 00:14:57.119
here, and requiring that it was
continuous and differentiably

00:14:57.119 --> 00:14:59.160
continuous-- that its
derivative was continuous--

00:14:59.160 --> 00:15:00.510
we found matching
conditions between

00:15:00.510 --> 00:15:01.926
the various
coefficients, and this

00:15:01.926 --> 00:15:03.440
was the solution in general.

00:15:03.440 --> 00:15:03.940
OK.

00:15:07.260 --> 00:15:12.090
Now, in particular,
this term, which

00:15:12.090 --> 00:15:17.830
corresponds to the component
of the wave function moving

00:15:17.830 --> 00:15:22.740
towards the barrier on the left
hand side, has amplitude 1.

00:15:22.740 --> 00:15:29.370
This term, which corresponds
to a wave on the left

00:15:29.370 --> 00:15:32.360
with negative momentum,
so moving to the left,

00:15:32.360 --> 00:15:35.390
has amplitude k minus i
alpha over k plus i alpha,

00:15:35.390 --> 00:15:39.470
where h bar squared
k squared upon 2m

00:15:39.470 --> 00:15:44.100
is equal to-- that's just the
energy, e-- and h bar squared

00:15:44.100 --> 00:15:47.600
alpha squared over 2m--
that's on this side-- is

00:15:47.600 --> 00:15:48.590
equal to v0 minus e.

00:15:51.940 --> 00:15:54.640
But this, notably,
is a pure phase.

00:15:54.640 --> 00:15:58.484
And we understood that, so
we'll call this parameter r,

00:15:58.484 --> 00:15:59.900
because this is
the reflected wave

00:15:59.900 --> 00:16:02.100
and this is an amplitude
rather than a probability,

00:16:02.100 --> 00:16:03.183
so we'll call it little r.

00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:09.450
And we notice that
the probability

00:16:09.450 --> 00:16:12.285
that we get out-- good.

00:16:12.285 --> 00:16:13.910
So if we want to ask
the question, what

00:16:13.910 --> 00:16:16.368
is the transmission probability,
the probability that I get

00:16:16.368 --> 00:16:19.210
from far out here to far out
here, what is that probability?

00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:26.364
So if I consider a state that
starts out as a localized wave

00:16:26.364 --> 00:16:28.530
packet way out here and I
send it in but with energy

00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:30.250
below the barrier,
what's the probability

00:16:30.250 --> 00:16:32.460
that I'll get
arbitrarily far out here,

00:16:32.460 --> 00:16:35.880
that I will subsequently find
the particle very far out here?

00:16:35.880 --> 00:16:36.866
0, right, exactly.

00:16:36.866 --> 00:16:38.990
And you can see that because
here's the probability

00:16:38.990 --> 00:16:40.910
amplitude, the norm
squared is the probability

00:16:40.910 --> 00:16:43.610
density as a function
of the position.

00:16:43.610 --> 00:16:46.470
And it goes like a constant
times e to the minus alpha x.

00:16:46.470 --> 00:16:48.770
For large x, this
exponential kills us.

00:16:48.770 --> 00:16:52.540
And we made that more precise
by talking about the current.

00:16:52.540 --> 00:16:54.330
We said look, the
current that gets

00:16:54.330 --> 00:16:58.980
transmitted is equal to-- that's
a funny way to write things.

00:16:58.980 --> 00:17:00.840
H bar-- sorry.

00:17:00.840 --> 00:17:02.520
The current that
gets transmitted,

00:17:02.520 --> 00:17:10.650
which equal to h bar upon
2mi psi complex conjugate dx

00:17:10.650 --> 00:17:17.936
psi minus psi dx psi complex
conjugate on the right.

00:17:17.936 --> 00:17:21.359
So we'll put right,
right, right, right.

00:17:21.359 --> 00:17:23.859
This is just equal to
0, and the easiest way

00:17:23.859 --> 00:17:25.359
to see that is
something you already

00:17:25.359 --> 00:17:27.839
showed on a problem set.

00:17:27.839 --> 00:17:29.630
The current vanishes
when the wave function

00:17:29.630 --> 00:17:31.650
can be made real up to a phase.

00:17:31.650 --> 00:17:35.960
And since this is some
number, but in particular it's

00:17:35.960 --> 00:17:37.870
an overall constant
complex number,

00:17:37.870 --> 00:17:39.310
and this is a real
wave function,

00:17:39.310 --> 00:17:41.140
we know that this is 0.

00:17:41.140 --> 00:17:43.640
So the transmitted
current out here is 0.

00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:45.950
The flux of particles moving
out to the right is 0.

00:17:48.876 --> 00:17:50.250
So nothing gets
out to the right.

00:17:50.250 --> 00:17:53.040
So that was for the energy
less than the potential,

00:17:53.040 --> 00:17:56.440
and we've now
re-derived this result,

00:17:56.440 --> 00:17:57.580
the classical prediction.

00:17:57.580 --> 00:18:01.305
So the classical prediction
worked pretty well.

00:18:01.305 --> 00:18:04.100
Now, importantly,
in general, we also

00:18:04.100 --> 00:18:06.537
wanted to define the
transmission probability

00:18:06.537 --> 00:18:08.120
a little more
carefully, and I'm going

00:18:08.120 --> 00:18:09.850
to define the
transmission probability

00:18:09.850 --> 00:18:12.270
as the current of
transmitted particles

00:18:12.270 --> 00:18:15.580
on the right divided by the
current of probability that

00:18:15.580 --> 00:18:18.460
was incident.

00:18:18.460 --> 00:18:21.450
And similarly, we can
define a probability

00:18:21.450 --> 00:18:23.640
that the particle
reflects, which

00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:27.320
is the ratio of the reflected
current, the current

00:18:27.320 --> 00:18:30.650
of the reflected beam,
to the incident current.

00:18:36.370 --> 00:18:38.600
So this is going to be the
transmission probability

00:18:38.600 --> 00:18:39.891
and the reflection probability.

00:18:42.721 --> 00:18:43.220
Yeah.

