And just for normalization,
we know that the transmission

01:08:11.310 --> 01:08:12.976
probability can never
be greater than 1,

01:08:12.976 --> 01:08:15.180
so it's got to be
between 1 and 0.

01:08:15.180 --> 01:08:19.260
So here's 0 and 0.

01:08:19.260 --> 01:08:22.207
We're remaining agnostic
about this for the moment.

01:08:22.207 --> 01:08:24.540
So let's start thinking about
what this plot looks like.

01:08:24.540 --> 01:08:26.620
First off, what does
it look like at 1?

01:08:26.620 --> 01:08:29.020
So when epsilon
goes to 1, this is

01:08:29.020 --> 01:08:31.380
going to 0, that's bad
because it's in a denominator.

01:08:31.380 --> 01:08:34.130
But upstairs, this
is going to 0,

01:08:34.130 --> 01:08:37.149
and sine squared of something
when it's becoming small

01:08:37.149 --> 01:08:39.210
goes like-- well, sine
goes like that thing.

01:08:39.210 --> 01:08:41.840
So sine squared goes like
this quantity squared.

01:08:41.840 --> 01:08:44.100
So sine squared goes
like g0 squared,

01:08:44.100 --> 01:08:47.260
this goes like 1
over-- this is going

01:08:47.260 --> 01:08:50.270
like g0 squared epsilon
minus 1 square root quantity

