01:10:15.930 --> 01:10:16.850
so that's kind of worrying.

01:10:16.850 --> 01:10:18.390
If this is very,
very large, this

01:10:18.390 --> 01:10:19.960
is a rapidly
oscillating function.

01:10:19.960 --> 01:10:22.796
However, it's being divided
by roughly epsilon squared.

01:10:22.796 --> 01:10:25.170
So something that goes between
0 and 1 divided by epsilon

01:10:25.170 --> 01:10:28.090
squared, as epsilon
gets large, becomes 0.

01:10:28.090 --> 01:10:30.560
And so we get 1 over
