the 1 over epsilon times

01:10:43.900 --> 01:10:44.577
some constant.

01:10:44.577 --> 01:10:46.160
But in fact, we have
the sine squared,

01:10:46.160 --> 01:10:47.868
and the sine squared
is making it wiggle.

01:10:47.868 --> 01:10:51.875
And the frequency
of the wiggle is g0,

01:10:51.875 --> 01:10:53.500
except that it's not
linear in epsilon,

01:10:53.500 --> 01:10:55.342
it's linear in square
root of epsilon.

01:10:55.342 --> 01:10:57.550
So as epsilon gets larger,
the square root of epsilon

01:10:57.550 --> 01:11:00.740
is getting larger
less than linearly.

01:11:00.740 --> 01:11:03.650
So what that's telling you is
if you looked at root epsilon,

01:11:03.650 --> 01:11:05.290
you would see it
with even period.

01:11:05.290 --> 01:11:06.840
But we don't have
root epsilon, we're

01:11:06.840 --> 01:11:08.464
plugging this as a
function of epsilon.

01:11:08.464 --> 01:11:10.910
So it's not even period,
