01:11:17.984 --> 01:11:18.650
It goes to zero.

01:11:18.650 --> 01:11:20.108
And what happens
when this is zero?

01:11:22.280 --> 01:11:23.700
Yeah, t is 1.

01:11:23.700 --> 01:11:27.190
So every time sine is 0,
i.e., for sufficient values

01:11:27.190 --> 01:11:31.282
when root epsilon is a multiple
of pi determined by g0,

01:11:31.282 --> 01:11:32.240
transmission goes to 1.

01:11:32.240 --> 01:11:33.790
It becomes perfect.

01:11:33.790 --> 01:11:35.880
So in fact, instead
of doing-- wow.

01:11:39.210 --> 01:11:45.780
Instead of doing this, what
it does is it does this.

